body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

The following Verilog have: `ERROR: Found 4 unproven $equiv cells in 'equiv_status -assert'.` with itself.

```verilog
module top_mod(
  input        clock,
  input        reset,
  output [3:0] tmp30,
  input  [3:0] inp_i
);
  reg [3:0] _tmp4;
  reg [3:0] tmp7;
  reg [3:0] tmp8;
  reg [3:0] tmp10;
  reg [3:0] tmp19;
  assign tmp30 = tmp19;
  always @(posedge clock) begin
    if (reset) begin
      _tmp4 <= 4'h0;
      tmp7 <= 4'h0;
      tmp8 <= 4'h0;
      tmp10 <= 4'h0;
      tmp19 <= 4'h0;
    end else begin
      _tmp4 <= inp_i;
      tmp7 <= _tmp4;
      tmp8 <= tmp7;
      tmp10 <= tmp8;
      tmp19 <= tmp10;
    end
  end
endmodule
```

```bash
yosys -q -p "
  read_verilog top_mod.v
  rename top_mod top1
  proc
  memory
  flatten top1
  hierarchy -top top1
  read_verilog top_mod.v
  rename top_mod top2
  proc
  memory
  flatten top2
  equiv_make top1 top2 equiv
  hierarchy -top equiv
  clean -purge
  equiv_simple -short -undef
  equiv_induct
  equiv_status -assert
"
```

`Yosys 0.9+3911 (git sha1 58a57551, clang 11.0.1 -fPIC -Os)`

## Expected behavior

to be equivalent with itself

`ERROR: Found 4 unproven $equiv cells in 'equiv_status -assert'.`

## Actual behavior

not equivalent to itself

